VESICULAR STOMATITIS, HORSES - USA (COLORADO) (03)
**************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Vesicular stomatitis, horses - USA (Colorado) 980730002322
Vesicular stomatitis, horses - USA (Colorado) (02) 980730082256
Date: Tue, 4 Aug 1998 17:42:11 -0500
Source: Vesicular Stomatitis Weekly Update Number 11
<http://www.aphis.usda.gov/vs/ep/>
Via: Martin Hugh-Jones <mehj2020@vt8200.vetmed.lsu.edu>

The following information is accurate up to 4:30 PM(MDT), Friday, July 31,
1998
Below is a summary of investigations as of July 31, 1998:
Colorado reported eight new VSV investigations during the week ending July
31. Four of these were VSV positive premises; three in Weld County and one
in Adams County. There are now eleven positive VSV premises in Colorado.
[In all other states the disease is presently inactive
Arizona reported no new VSV investigations for the week ending July 31,
1998. Two VSV positive premises were released from quarantine, one each in
Mojave and Santa Cruz Counties. This brings Arizona's total to thirteen
positive premises quarantined for VSV.
New Mexico reports no new VSV investigations during this reporting period.
The number of positive premises quarantined for VSV remains at nine.
Texas' only positive VSV premises, located in Reeves County, was released
from quarantine on July 31, 1998. Its only pending investigation is now
negative for VSV.
This update reflects only the investigations in case positive states after
the index case was reported.
All positive cases in the four affected States have been of the equine
species.
